	     Cape Town -  President Jacob Zuma is expected to address the
nation on the current situation in Zimbabwe. This comes as President
Robert Mugabe is said to be under heavy guard after soldiers cordoned off the
parliament building and the defence headquarters, as the security situation
deteriorates in the southern African country. Zuma
is the current chairperson of SADC. More to follow 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  